                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12682119" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Sun, 15 Mar 2009 02:35:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If the setDefaultStyle() method is not used, then the class is not thread-hostile, so the Javadoc should at least point this out.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The get/setDefaultStyle() methods should really be synch, otherwise there is no guarantee what one thread will get when another sets.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If this were done, then it would be safe to call the set() method before any use is made of the class.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Users that provide a non-null ToStringStyle to constructors and static methods should not be affected by changes to the default style, so perhaps the constructors should enforce this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12697428" author="bayard" created="Thu, 9 Apr 2009 08:20:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Rewrite for 3.0 to deal with/remove the static variable?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12770232" author="scolebourne" created="Mon, 26 Oct 2009 22:07:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Variable made volatile.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I propose we close this call.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12801118" author="bayard" created="Sat, 16 Jan 2010 07:43:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing per Stephen&apos;s commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
